Date: 0/0/1926
Source: Weeds of New Zealand
Author: HILGENDORF
Vol / Page: 86
Edition: 1967
Quote: CALIFORNIAN POPPY (<i>Eschsholzia [Eschscholtzia] californica</i>), often called eschscholtzia, and sometimes Johnny-go-to-bed, on account perhaps of its nightcap-like calyces, is found in profusion on the shingly river-beds of the South Island.
